54.5	Death_Race_2000	Death Race 2000	Death Race 2000 is a 1975 cult action film directed by Paul Bartel, and starring David Carradine, Simone Griffeth and Sylvester Stallone. The film takes place in a dystopian American society in the year 2000, where the murderous Transcontinental Road Race has become a form of national entertainment. The screenplay is based on the short story The Racer by Ib Melchior.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/40/Deathrace2000poster.jpg/215px-Deathrace2000poster.jpg
